text: Grevillea cheilocarpa is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to a small area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia. The shrub typically grows to in height and has non-glaucous branchlets. It has simple undissected flat leaves that have an obovate shape and are long and wide. ==See also== * List of Grevillea species ==References== cheilocarpa Category:Proteales of Australia Category:Eudicots of Western Australia Category:Taxa named by Robert Owen Makinson
title: Grevillea cheilocarpa
